OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Roy Hayward
OL,5,F"Arromanches was the main part where
OL,6,Fwe were landing. We were already
OL,7,Fhaving a lot of casualties and so I
OL,8,Fwas called up to be the radio operator
OL,9,Fin the tank crew."
OL,11,FA few days later the Sherman tank Mr
OL,12,FHayward was in took a direct hit from
OL,13,Fan enemy shell.
OL,15,F"On this particular morning we were in
OL,16,Fa lane and an infantry sergeant
OL,17,Fapproached us and said he was being
OL,18,Fheld up by something, probably a tank
OL,19,Fso we took him on board to show us
OL,20,Fwhere he was having the problem.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
